{"questionId": "6f7157fc-7e47-4e83-add3-e372915177ec_21", "correctAnswer": "32.5,65/2", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Calculate the slope from the table", "content": "Using points $(2, -\\frac{183}{10})$ and $(4, -\\frac{171}{10})$:<br/>$$m = \\frac{-\\frac{171}{10} - (-\\frac{183}{10})}{4 - 2} = \\frac{\\frac{12}{10}}{2} = \\frac{12}{20} = \\frac{3}{5}$$", "formula": "$$m = \\frac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}$$"}, {"title": "Write the equation of the line", "content": "Using point $(2, -\\frac{183}{10})$ and slope $\\frac{3}{5}$, apply point-slope form:<br/>$$y - (-\\frac{183}{10}) = \\frac{3}{5}(x - 2)$$<br/>$$y + \\frac{183}{10} = \\frac{3}{5}x - \\frac{6}{5}$$<br/>Convert $-\\frac{6}{5}$ to tenths: $-\\frac{6}{5} = -\\frac{12}{10}$<br/>$$y = \\frac{3}{5}x - \\frac{12}{10} - \\frac{183}{10}$$<br/>$$y = \\frac{3}{5}x - \\frac{195}{10} = \\frac{3}{5}x - \\frac{39}{2}$$", "formula": "$$y - y_1 = m(x - x_1)$$"}, {"title": "Find the x-intercept by setting y = 0", "content": "At the x-intercept, $y = 0$:<br/>$$0 = \\frac{3}{5}x - \\frac{39}{2}$$<br/>$$\\frac{3}{5}x = \\frac{39}{2}$$<br/>$$x = \\frac{39}{2} \\cdot \\frac{5}{3} = \\frac{195}{6} = \\frac{65}{2} = 32.5$$<br/>The answer is <strong>32.5,65/2</strong>."}]}